
--------------------------------------------------
MODULE 1: AUTHENTICATION (STAFF ACCESS)
--------------------------------------------------

Goal:
Improve security and usability for cinema managers accessing the system.

Enhanced Features:

1. Password Security Validation
- Enforce strong password requirements:
  - Minimum length: 8 characters
  - At least one uppercase letter
  - At least one number
  - At least one special character
- Prevent reuse of recent passwords.

2. Failed Login Protection
- Lock account after 5 failed login attempts.
- Display clear message:
  "Too many failed login attempts. Please contact the administrator."

3. Login Activity Tracking
- Store last login timestamp for each user.
- Display on dashboard:
  "Last Login: [Date and Time]"

4. Role-Based Access (Optional but recommended)
Support future roles:
- admin
- manager

Permissions example:
admin → full system access
manager → manage movies and screenings only

5. Session Expiry Warning
Before session timeout show notification:
"Your session will expire in 5 minutes."

6. Password Reset Support
Allow password reset via secure token:
Forgot Password → Email → Reset Link → New Password

--------------------------------------------------
MODULE 2: HALL MANAGEMENT (PHYSICAL SPACE)
--------------------------------------------------

Goal:
Provide cinema managers with clear control over theatre halls
and seating configurations.

Enhanced Features:

1. Automatic Hall Capacity Calculation
Capacity is automatically computed:

capacity = rows × columns

Display example:

Hall A
Rows: 10
Columns: 15
Capacity: 150 seats

2. Seat Type Configuration
Allow different seat categories:

Regular Seat
VIP Seat
Wheelchair Accessible Seat

Example distribution:

Regular: 130
VIP: 15
Wheelchair: 5

3. Hall Status Indicators
Visual hall states:

ACTIVE
UNDER MAINTENANCE
CLEANING

Recommended color indicators:

Green → Active
Red → Maintenance
Yellow → Cleaning

4. Maintenance Scheduling
Managers can schedule maintenance windows.

Fields:
Maintenance Start Date
Maintenance End Date
Maintenance Reason

Example:

Hall B
Maintenance Period: 15 Mar – 16 Mar
Reason: Projector replacement

5. Seating Layout Preview
Display seating as grid preview.

Example:

Row A: [O][O][O][W][O]
Row B: [O][O][O][O][O]
Row C: [V][V][V][O][O]

Legend:
O = Regular
V = VIP
W = Wheelchair

--------------------------------------------------
MODULE 3: MOVIE MANAGEMENT (CONTENT)
--------------------------------------------------

Goal:
Provide cinema managers with an organized movie catalogue.

Enhanced Features:

1. Movie Poster Support
Allow uploading or linking poster images.

Display poster in movie list view.

2. Movie Status Categories

Now Showing
Coming Soon
Archived

Behavior:

Coming Soon → cannot schedule until release date
Archived → no new screenings allowed

3. Duration Display and Scheduling Preview
Display movie duration clearly.

Example:

Duration: 120 minutes
Expected End Time: 4:00 PM

4. Genre Tags
Allow multiple genres.

Examples:

Action
Comedy
Animation
Family
Horror
Sci-Fi

5. Movie Search and Filtering

Search by:
Title
Genre
Status
Release Year

Example filters:

Search: Avengers
Genre: Action
Status: Now Showing

6. Safe Deletion Validation

Prevent deleting movies with scheduled screenings.

Instead of generic error:

"Cannot delete movie with upcoming screenings."

Provide helpful information:

"This movie has 5 future screenings scheduled.
Please remove or reschedule them before deleting."

--------------------------------------------------
MODULE 4: SCREENING SCHEDULING (OPERATIONS)
--------------------------------------------------

Goal:
Allow managers to schedule screenings easily while preventing
scheduling mistakes.

Enhanced Features:

1. Automatic End Time Calculation

Managers enter:

Start Time

System calculates:

End Time = Start Time + Movie Duration

Example:

Start Time: 2:00 PM
Duration: 120 minutes
End Time: 4:00 PM

2. Conflict Detection with Detailed Error Messages

Instead of generic rejection:

Provide conflict details:

Scheduling Conflict

Hall A already has a screening:
Movie: Interstellar
Time: 2:00 PM – 4:30 PM

Please select another time slot.

3. Daily Schedule Overview

Provide simple timeline view:

Hall A

10:00 AM – Movie A
2:00 PM – Movie B
6:00 PM – Movie C

4. Cleaning Buffer Time

Add optional buffer between screenings.

Example:

Cleaning Buffer = 15 minutes

If movie ends at 4:00 PM

Next screening allowed:

4:15 PM

5. Screening Status Tracking

Screenings may have states:

Scheduled
Cancelled
Completed

Managers can cancel screenings if necessary.

6. Duplicate Screening Prevention

Prevent accidental duplicates.

Example duplicates:

Same movie
Same hall
Same time

